      "text": "A 54-year-old woman with a history of deep-vein thrombosis and uveitis presents with pain and burning in the genital area that started 2 weeks ago. One week before the onset of those symptoms, she noticed multiple painful oral lesions on her tongue, buccal mucosa, and soft palate. She reports that she has had similar lesions 3 to 5 times per year for the past several years. Her intake of food and fluids has not been affected.\nPhysical examination reveals several aphthous ulcers on the tongue, buccal mucosa (figure), and labia majora. A swab for herpes simplex virus of the current buccal-mucosa lesion is negative. Laboratory work reveals an antinuclear antibody titer of 1:40 and negative findings for anti-double-stranded DNA, anti-Smith, and HIV antibodies.\nThe patient is treated with oral prednisone 0.5 mg/kg. The lesions resolve, and she tapers off prednisone over the next 4 weeks.\nWhich one of the following treatments is most appropriate for preventing recurrence of this patient’s genital lesions?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Acyclovir"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Prednisone"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Hydroxychloroquine"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Fluconazole"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Colchicine"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 5,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pm0Lgg&anker=Z5a0cef096920d39da0f3cc2cbeb0fc9b\" data-learningcard-id=\"pm0Lgg\" data-anker=\"Z5a0cef096920d39da0f3cc2cbeb0fc9b\" data-section-id=\"DBX1100\" data-sememe-id=\"6WYjmL\">Acyclovir</a> would be appropriate treatment only for <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulcers</span> caused by <span data-sememe-id=\"yE1dyi0\">herpes simplex virus</span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z712b2dc74159254df543699d457da232\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z712b2dc74159254df543699d457da232\" data-section-id=\"F8bgov\">Systemic glucocorticoids</a>, other <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qM0Cpg&anker=Zbe2f99ecf3c73cc831a5c78ef2226ffd\" data-learningcard-id=\"qM0Cpg\" data-anker=\"Zbe2f99ecf3c73cc831a5c78ef2226ffd\" data-sememe-id=\"so0tWS\">immunosuppressive drugs</a>, or both are indicated for the treatment of moderate-to-severe or refractory mucocutaneous disease, <span data-sememe-id=\"LBewYYa\">gastrointestinal</span> disease, severe <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=JO0stT&anker=Zd5d2643ba7468816c97698c34922eabe\" data-learningcard-id=\"JO0stT\" data-anker=\"Zd5d2643ba7468816c97698c34922eabe\" data-section-id=\"ywXdlZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"azaQrM\">uveitis</a>, vascular disease (arterial or venous), or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lp0vpS&anker=Z0111aade770ed6f7d136b455de1d6c1f\" data-learningcard-id=\"lp0vpS\" data-anker=\"Z0111aade770ed6f7d136b455de1d6c1f\" data-section-id=\"1Cc2Ie0\" data-sememe-id=\"6SXj0B\">central nervous system</a> disease. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-sememe-id=\"4L03Bg\">Glucocorticoids</a> have multiple toxicities with long-term use and therefore are not a first-line choice for the prevention of recurrent mucocutaneous manifestations of Behçet disease.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=8M0Oqg&anker=Z05c386297810214a97ed39a73e001841\" data-learningcard-id=\"8M0Oqg\" data-anker=\"Z05c386297810214a97ed39a73e001841\" data-section-id=\"72X4Qx\" data-sememe-id=\"221TST0\">Hydroxychloroquine</a> might be an appropriate treatment for oral <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulcers</span> in patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dT0op2&anker=Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-learningcard-id=\"dT0op2\" data-anker=\"Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-sememe-id=\"6q0jzS\">systemic lupus erythematosus</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dT0op2&anker=Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-learningcard-id=\"dT0op2\" data-anker=\"Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-sememe-id=\"6q0jzS\">SLE</a>), who often develop painless nasal and/or oral <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulcers</span>. However, this medication is not effective in preventing mucocutaneous lesions in Behçet disease.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=6m0jgg&anker=Za11c477e8dbd65003749c47c4f14d0ef\" data-learningcard-id=\"6m0jgg\" data-anker=\"Za11c477e8dbd65003749c47c4f14d0ef\" data-section-id=\"_315Og0\" data-sememe-id=\"5WYiNL\">Fluconazole</a> can be used for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rf0fn2&anker=Z8722414bff52e7a5dcc1ef2deae7ddbf\" data-learningcard-id=\"rf0fn2\" data-anker=\"Z8722414bff52e7a5dcc1ef2deae7ddbf\" data-section-id=\"Cedqa60\" data-sememe-id=\"eAYxi7\">oral candidiasis</a>, which at times can cause <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulceration</span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) CORRECT:</h4>Recurrent oral and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=IM0YJg&anker=Zd061df563924ac065af14111ea9f656a\" data-learningcard-id=\"IM0YJg\" data-anker=\"Zd061df563924ac065af14111ea9f656a\" data-section-id=\"N-X-x00\">genital lesions</a> in a patient with a history of ocular inflammatory disease are highly suggestive of Behçet disease.<br><br>Optimal treatment for mucocutaneous Behçet disease is not established. Topical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-sememe-id=\"4L03Bg\">glucocorticoids</a> may be used to treat isolated lesions, whereas <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z712b2dc74159254df543699d457da232\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z712b2dc74159254df543699d457da232\" data-section-id=\"F8bgov\">systemic glucocorticoids</a> are often needed to treat refractory or more widespread lesions.<br><br>Once the lesions are healed, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=YT0n62&anker=Za7ec01fa067126441bfca71d4f27200f\" data-learningcard-id=\"YT0n62\" data-anker=\"Za7ec01fa067126441bfca71d4f27200f\" data-section-id=\"NJ1-830\" data-sememe-id=\"8J0ODS\">colchicine</a> is widely used as a first-line treatment for the prevention of mild-to-moderate mucocutaneous disease, and its use is supported by some but not all <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=1j02zf&anker=Z23a4f338ff0ec4559eef3dadbc87fa94\" data-learningcard-id=\"1j02zf\" data-anker=\"Z23a4f338ff0ec4559eef3dadbc87fa94\" data-section-id=\"apcQLW0\" data-sememe-id=\"rsafwN\">randomized</a> clinical trials. More recently, apremilast (an oral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=em0xeg&anker=Z370d7cafd3cc0cc516bacf9c5cad042c\" data-learningcard-id=\"em0xeg\" data-anker=\"Z370d7cafd3cc0cc516bacf9c5cad042c\" data-section-id=\"jtb_Wv\">phosphodiesterase type 4 inhibitor</a>) has been shown to be effective in reducing the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Js0sDh&anker=Za75cae58612d57021fbad9a9bc842614\" data-learningcard-id=\"Js0sDh\" data-anker=\"Za75cae58612d57021fbad9a9bc842614\" data-section-id=\"9fWNok0\" data-sememe-id=\"U-bb9w\">incidence</a> and severity of oral <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulcers</span> in patients with Behçet disease.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> The most appropriate treatment for preventing recurrence of mild-to-moderate mucocutaneous Behçet disease is <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=YT0n62&anker=Za7ec01fa067126441bfca71d4f27200f\" data-learningcard-id=\"YT0n62\" data-anker=\"Za7ec01fa067126441bfca71d4f27200f\" data-section-id=\"NJ1-830\" data-sememe-id=\"8J0ODS\">colchicine</a>.</div>",
