      "text": "A 40-year-old man presents to the emergency department (ED) with a 2-day history of right calf swelling and tenderness. He reports no chest pain, shortness of breath, or history of immobilization or malignancy. He notes that he had similar symptoms in the left leg 5 years ago, which was diagnosed as deep-vein thrombosis and treated with dabigatran for 3 months.\nOn further history, he describes frequent oral aphthous ulcers, a few episodes of genital ulcers, and two episodes of uveitis treated with prednisolone eye drops. Some of the episodes of ulcers have been associated with knee and ankle swelling, but the patient denies any back pain. He reports that he is sexually active in a monogamous relationship and is of Turkish descent.\nHis vital signs are within normal limits. Three oral aphthae are evident on head and neck examination, and genitourinary examination reveals a painful 2-cm scrotal ulcer. The right calf measures 3 cm larger than the left in circumference, with a tender palpable cord. The rest of the examination is normal.\nLaboratory testing reveals a hemoglobin concentration of 14.0 g/dL (reference range, 13.5–17.5), an erythrocyte sedimentation rate of 50 mm/hour (0–17), and a C-reactive protein level of 40.5 mg/liter (0.08–3.10). The rest of the complete blood count and metabolic profile is normal. Testing is negative for antiphospholipid antibody and beta-2-glycoprotein immunoglobulin G/M. Anticardiolipin antibody levels are 16 GPL units for IgG and 13 GPL units for IgM (0–15).\nA vascular Doppler ultrasound of the right lower extremity reveals deep-vein thrombosis involving the popliteal and superficial femoral veins. The patient is given dabigatran in the ED.\nWhich one of the following tests is most likely to be positive in this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "HLA-B27 testing"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Antinuclear antibody test"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Testing for activated protein C resistance"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Pathergy skin test"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Rapid plasma reagin test"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0T0e62&anker=Z004554eda6fc600767f0d5dbaca1925d\" data-learningcard-id=\"0T0e62\" data-anker=\"Z004554eda6fc600767f0d5dbaca1925d\" data-sememe-id=\"VP0GdT\">Reactive arthritis</a>, which is most commonly seen in individuals with the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=J30sjf&anker=Z0ece044a192244eb89317e00c4cfdcd6\" data-learningcard-id=\"J30sjf\" data-anker=\"Z0ece044a192244eb89317e00c4cfdcd6\" data-section-id=\"whchTX0\" data-sememe-id=\"0zYer7\">HLA-B27</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=y50d5g&anker=Z94dd69013513c2616894ef6dbe01d837\" data-learningcard-id=\"y50d5g\" data-anker=\"Z94dd69013513c2616894ef6dbe01d837\" data-section-id=\"xWcEnY0\">gene</a>, can be associated with ocular complications such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=JO0stT&anker=Zd5d2643ba7468816c97698c34922eabe\" data-learningcard-id=\"JO0stT\" data-anker=\"Zd5d2643ba7468816c97698c34922eabe\" data-section-id=\"ywXdlZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"azaQrM\">uveitis</a> but not with the other features of this patient’s clinical presentation.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ul0pAT&anker=Z50118528301d2163a3a5d644e0e77a3d\" data-learningcard-id=\"ul0pAT\" data-anker=\"Z50118528301d2163a3a5d644e0e77a3d\" data-section-id=\"yCXduZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"nYY7pn\">Antinuclear antibody</a> testing is often positive in patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dT0op2&anker=Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-learningcard-id=\"dT0op2\" data-anker=\"Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-sememe-id=\"6q0jzS\">systemic lupus erythematosus</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dT0op2&anker=Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-learningcard-id=\"dT0op2\" data-anker=\"Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-sememe-id=\"6q0jzS\">SLE</a>), and this condition can be associated with several of the features seen in this patient, including painless oral <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulcers</span>, small-<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Bo0zVS&anker=Z42dfc5649a4025fa49ffc6ebd8712c18\" data-learningcard-id=\"Bo0zVS\" data-anker=\"Z42dfc5649a4025fa49ffc6ebd8712c18\">joint</a> <span data-sememe-id=\"Z1WZ240\">arthritis</span>, and <span data-sememe-id=\"eybxVw\">thrombosis</span>, especially in the presence of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hR0c5f&anker=Zc64f6e326ddf58b2bc9a198ed8f87dd2\" data-learningcard-id=\"hR0c5f\" data-anker=\"Zc64f6e326ddf58b2bc9a198ed8f87dd2\" data-section-id=\"VqaGxl\" data-sememe-id=\"QJYuFJ\">antiphospholipid antibodies</a>. However, this patient is unlikely to have <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dT0op2&anker=Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-learningcard-id=\"dT0op2\" data-anker=\"Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-sememe-id=\"6q0jzS\">SLE</a> given his male sex, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=JO0stT&anker=Zd5d2643ba7468816c97698c34922eabe\" data-learningcard-id=\"JO0stT\" data-anker=\"Zd5d2643ba7468816c97698c34922eabe\" data-section-id=\"ywXdlZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"azaQrM\">uveitis</a> is not a common feature of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dT0op2&anker=Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-learningcard-id=\"dT0op2\" data-anker=\"Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-sememe-id=\"6q0jzS\">SLE</a>. Patients with Behçet disease rarely test positive for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ul0pAT&anker=Z50118528301d2163a3a5d644e0e77a3d\" data-learningcard-id=\"ul0pAT\" data-anker=\"Z50118528301d2163a3a5d644e0e77a3d\" data-section-id=\"yCXduZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"nYY7pn\">antinuclear antibodies</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>Although additional laboratory testing for other causes of a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=bo0H0S&anker=Z0f31154c63b8097e20cbfc0736fd665a\" data-learningcard-id=\"bo0H0S\" data-anker=\"Z0f31154c63b8097e20cbfc0736fd665a\" data-sememe-id=\"f0bk2H\">hypercoagulable state</a>, such as testing for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=bo0H0S&anker=Zb3e9772d6c6e5f2957269015016f5613\" data-learningcard-id=\"bo0H0S\" data-anker=\"Zb3e9772d6c6e5f2957269015016f5613\" data-section-id=\"2QcTvX0\">activated protein C resistance</a>, may be considered in this patient, his venous <span data-sememe-id=\"eybxVw\">thrombosis</span> is more likely to be related to his Behçet disease than to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=bo0H0S&anker=Zb3e9772d6c6e5f2957269015016f5613\" data-learningcard-id=\"bo0H0S\" data-anker=\"Zb3e9772d6c6e5f2957269015016f5613\" data-section-id=\"2QcTvX0\">activated protein C resistance</a> from a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=bo0H0S&anker=Za4fb4b16ae6356e33f0bd0538921c1f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"bo0H0S\" data-anker=\"Za4fb4b16ae6356e33f0bd0538921c1f3\" data-section-id=\"2QcTvX0\" data-sememe-id=\"Ew08kR\">factor V Leiden mutation</a>. He is therefore unlikely to have a positive result on this test. In addition, it should be noted that functional tests for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=bo0H0S&anker=Zb3e9772d6c6e5f2957269015016f5613\" data-learningcard-id=\"bo0H0S\" data-anker=\"Zb3e9772d6c6e5f2957269015016f5613\" data-section-id=\"2QcTvX0\">activated protein C resistance</a> may produce falsely normal results if patients are tested while taking <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Tm06Ug&anker=Zd24d1893c4171ccb765a3953d1de694a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Tm06Ug\" data-anker=\"Zd24d1893c4171ccb765a3953d1de694a\" data-section-id=\"fFbkhv\" data-sememe-id=\"bKcHUW0\">direct oral anticoagulants</a>; <span data-sememe-id=\"2E1TEi0\">genetic testing</span> may therefore be preferred in these cases.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>The diagnosis of Behçet disease should be considered when a patient presents with oral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Gk0B6T&anker=Zdc44f4b49d025f5c26e9b960116b7620\" data-learningcard-id=\"Gk0B6T\" data-anker=\"Zdc44f4b49d025f5c26e9b960116b7620\" data-sememe-id=\"Jnas8O\">aphthous ulcers</a> and any of several systemic features. Although there are currently no widely accepted diagnostic criteria for this condition, an international team has proposed the system outlined in the table below whereby a score ≥4 indicates Behçet disease. Ethnic groups with higher rates of Behçet disease include those of Mediterranean or East Asian descent.<br><br>This patient presents with oral and genital <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulcers</span>, vascular <span data-sememe-id=\"eybxVw\">thrombosis</span>, and a history of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=JO0stT&anker=Zd5d2643ba7468816c97698c34922eabe\" data-learningcard-id=\"JO0stT\" data-anker=\"Zd5d2643ba7468816c97698c34922eabe\" data-section-id=\"ywXdlZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"azaQrM\">uveitis</a> and <span data-sememe-id=\"Z1WZ240\">arthritis</span> — and therefore meets the diagnostic criteria for Behçet disease. Foregoing the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_t05T3&anker=Z92beef6f29f3a4b88f8b278c9e9672ea\" data-learningcard-id=\"_t05T3\" data-anker=\"Z92beef6f29f3a4b88f8b278c9e9672ea\" data-section-id=\"3JWSFm0\" data-sememe-id=\"7zY487\">pathergy skin test</a> may be reasonable, but if the test is performed, the likelihood of a positive result is around 50%. In addition to anticoagulation for deep-<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZK0ZUS&anker=Z6f8d5f3537f44c7bd7f1915d726b6360\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZK0ZUS\" data-anker=\"Z6f8d5f3537f44c7bd7f1915d726b6360\" data-section-id=\"WJcPGW0\">vein</a> <span data-sememe-id=\"eybxVw\">thrombosis</span>, management of this patient’s Behçet disease could include any of the following treatments: <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-sememe-id=\"4L03Bg\">glucocorticoids</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=YT0n62&anker=Za7ec01fa067126441bfca71d4f27200f\" data-learningcard-id=\"YT0n62\" data-anker=\"Za7ec01fa067126441bfca71d4f27200f\" data-section-id=\"NJ1-830\" data-sememe-id=\"8J0ODS\">colchicine</a> or apremilast (both are especially effective for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Gk0B6T&anker=Zdc44f4b49d025f5c26e9b960116b7620\" data-learningcard-id=\"Gk0B6T\" data-anker=\"Zdc44f4b49d025f5c26e9b960116b7620\" data-sememe-id=\"Jnas8O\">aphthous ulcers</a>), <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z9a90048189fed50cf6802d5d8b825cab\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z9a90048189fed50cf6802d5d8b825cab\" data-section-id=\"lW1vlf0\" data-sememe-id=\"h5acPO\">methotrexate</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4p03pS&anker=Z8eede753e92ff6605afa92fa899651fd\" data-learningcard-id=\"4p03pS\" data-anker=\"Z8eede753e92ff6605afa92fa899651fd\" data-section-id=\"D9c1pe0\">tumor necrosis factor</a> inhibitors.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> Vascular manifestations of Behçet disease include variable-size <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=fT0kJ2&anker=Z65c5d02013e50d4a2715ee8ae8d47b02\" data-learningcard-id=\"fT0kJ2\" data-anker=\"Z65c5d02013e50d4a2715ee8ae8d47b02\" data-sememe-id=\"iP0JeT\">vasculitis</a> and venous <span data-sememe-id=\"eybxVw\">thrombosis</span>.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_65f1daac529492.03029170.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sk0t6T&anker=Zede16ceb0c9d7241b84e3210bccb30ca\" data-learningcard-id=\"sk0t6T\" data-anker=\"Zede16ceb0c9d7241b84e3210bccb30ca\" data-section-id=\"vcbAVs\" data-sememe-id=\"S2aySP\">Primary syphilis</a>, which can be diagnosed with a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sk0t6T&anker=Z23f778ecfe4c2558c29327cf21aab5a9\" data-learningcard-id=\"sk0t6T\" data-anker=\"Z23f778ecfe4c2558c29327cf21aab5a9\" data-section-id=\"9cbNes\" data-sememe-id=\"vzYAu7\">rapid plasma reagin</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sk0t6T&anker=Z23f778ecfe4c2558c29327cf21aab5a9\" data-learningcard-id=\"sk0t6T\" data-anker=\"Z23f778ecfe4c2558c29327cf21aab5a9\" data-section-id=\"9cbNes\" data-sememe-id=\"vzYAu7\">RPR</a>) test, should be considered in patients with genital <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulcers</span>, but the <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulcers</span> associated with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sk0t6T&anker=Zede16ceb0c9d7241b84e3210bccb30ca\" data-learningcard-id=\"sk0t6T\" data-anker=\"Zede16ceb0c9d7241b84e3210bccb30ca\" data-section-id=\"vcbAVs\" data-sememe-id=\"S2aySP\">primary syphilis</a> are typically painless and are not associated with systemic symptoms.</div>",
