      "text": "A 28-year-old man presents to the emergency department with severe eye pain and blurred vision that started 2 days ago. He reports a 3-year history of recurrent painful mouth sores occurring every 2–3 months and lasting about 2 weeks each time. The patient also mentions having similar painful sores on his scrotum twice in the past year that healed with scarring. Physical examination reveals bilateral conjunctival injection, and ophthalmologic consultation confirms anterior uveitis. Which additional finding would most strongly support the suspected diagnosis?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Positive rheumatoid factor and elevated CRP"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Positive pathergy test showing erythematous papule formation 48 hours after needle prick"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Symmetric polyarticular joint involvement affecting small joints of hands and feet"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Positive ANA and anti-dsDNA antibodies"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Vesicular lesions with positive Tzanck smear showing multinucleated giant cells"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Ze58aa99e36800145f14fde1821e34632\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Ze58aa99e36800145f14fde1821e34632\">Laboratory studies</a> in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_t05T3&anker=Za75c3a0dc1419ba76a2754ac89f9e9f8\" data-learningcard-id=\"_t05T3\" data-anker=\"Za75c3a0dc1419ba76a2754ac89f9e9f8\" data-sememe-id=\"KoaU1l\">Behcet disease</a> typically reveal absent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=x50Emg&anker=Z07ff4a8efdae49ba17ed2b65e3db534d\" data-learningcard-id=\"x50Emg\" data-anker=\"Z07ff4a8efdae49ba17ed2b65e3db534d\" data-section-id=\"S_Xyn00\" data-sememe-id=\"2rbTgE\">autoantibodies</a>, including <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-f0DK2&anker=Z078b973a95f28edb3a0bd5ce05b32655\" data-learningcard-id=\"-f0DK2\" data-anker=\"Z078b973a95f28edb3a0bd5ce05b32655\" data-section-id=\"Ej08XT\" data-sememe-id=\"TJ06tS\">rheumatoid factor</a>. While <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Zb4c8f1543d29d334dcb50edc6af8a2a2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Zb4c8f1543d29d334dcb50edc6af8a2a2\" data-section-id=\"-V1DCf0\" data-sememe-id=\"JVYsvL\">inflammatory markers</a> like <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Z51ad1e101a45a8de708a6dda0321755d\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Z51ad1e101a45a8de708a6dda0321755d\" data-section-id=\"-V1DCf0\" data-sememe-id=\"IVYYDL\">CRP</a> may be elevated, they are nonspecific, and normal values do not exclude the diagnosis.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- A positive <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_t05T3&anker=Z92beef6f29f3a4b88f8b278c9e9672ea\" data-learningcard-id=\"_t05T3\" data-anker=\"Z92beef6f29f3a4b88f8b278c9e9672ea\" data-section-id=\"3JWSFm0\" data-sememe-id=\"7zY487\">pathergy test</a>, in which an <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"3wYSir\">erythematous</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"sCatt5\">papule</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"uCapF5\">pustule</a> appears 48 hours after a 5-mm <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> prick with a 20-gauge needle, is one of the additional criteria in the International Study Group diagnostic criteria for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_t05T3&anker=Za75c3a0dc1419ba76a2754ac89f9e9f8\" data-learningcard-id=\"_t05T3\" data-anker=\"Za75c3a0dc1419ba76a2754ac89f9e9f8\" data-sememe-id=\"KoaU1l\">Behcet disease</a>. This patient already has the mandatory criterion (≥ 3 episodes of oral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Gk0B6T&anker=Zdc44f4b49d025f5c26e9b960116b7620\" data-learningcard-id=\"Gk0B6T\" data-anker=\"Zdc44f4b49d025f5c26e9b960116b7620\" data-sememe-id=\"Jnas8O\">aphthous ulcers</a> in 12 months) plus two additional criteria (ocular manifestations and recurrent genital <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulceration</span>), making <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_t05T3&anker=Za75c3a0dc1419ba76a2754ac89f9e9f8\" data-learningcard-id=\"_t05T3\" data-anker=\"Za75c3a0dc1419ba76a2754ac89f9e9f8\" data-sememe-id=\"KoaU1l\">Behcet disease</a> the most likely diagnosis.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_t05T3&anker=Za75c3a0dc1419ba76a2754ac89f9e9f8\" data-learningcard-id=\"_t05T3\" data-anker=\"Za75c3a0dc1419ba76a2754ac89f9e9f8\" data-sememe-id=\"KoaU1l\">Behcet disease</a>, which is consistent with this patient's presentation, typically causes nonerosive, nondeforming, asymmetric <span data-sememe-id=\"-cWDU40\">monoarthritis</span> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dv0o_3&anker=Z6ac1ebd04a86b45a2fc307bbd42aad01\" data-learningcard-id=\"dv0o_3\" data-anker=\"Z6ac1ebd04a86b45a2fc307bbd42aad01\" data-section-id=\"wOdhuJ0\" data-sememe-id=\"WhVP180\">oligoarthritis</a> affecting the knees, ankles, hands, and wrists. Symmetric polyarticular involvement of <span data-sememe-id=\"FcWgV40\">small joints</span> is more characteristic of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-f0DK2&anker=Z0bdeffd118af8bb1971e0d4ae4d7881e\" data-learningcard-id=\"-f0DK2\" data-anker=\"Z0bdeffd118af8bb1971e0d4ae4d7881e\" data-sememe-id=\"WP0PdT\">rheumatoid arthritis</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=x50Emg&anker=Z07ff4a8efdae49ba17ed2b65e3db534d\" data-learningcard-id=\"x50Emg\" data-anker=\"Z07ff4a8efdae49ba17ed2b65e3db534d\" data-section-id=\"S_Xyn00\" data-sememe-id=\"2rbTgE\">Autoantibodies</a> such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ul0pAT&anker=Z50118528301d2163a3a5d644e0e77a3d\" data-learningcard-id=\"ul0pAT\" data-anker=\"Z50118528301d2163a3a5d644e0e77a3d\" data-section-id=\"yCXduZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"nYY7pn\">ANA</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dT0op2&anker=Z5327a43b4c8b784329da9e81caee6987\" data-learningcard-id=\"dT0op2\" data-anker=\"Z5327a43b4c8b784329da9e81caee6987\" data-section-id=\"mk0VoT\" data-sememe-id=\"uq0pZh\">anti-dsDNA</a> are usually absent in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_t05T3&anker=Za75c3a0dc1419ba76a2754ac89f9e9f8\" data-learningcard-id=\"_t05T3\" data-anker=\"Za75c3a0dc1419ba76a2754ac89f9e9f8\" data-sememe-id=\"KoaU1l\">Behcet disease</a>, which helps differentiate it from other autoimmune conditions like <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dT0op2&anker=Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-learningcard-id=\"dT0op2\" data-anker=\"Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-sememe-id=\"6q0jzS\">systemic lupus erythematosus</a>. Their absence, not their presence, supports the diagnosis.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z7c5fd3823051fa560edec27fe227985f\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z7c5fd3823051fa560edec27fe227985f\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"tCaXF5\">Vesicular lesions</a> with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=VP0GdT&anker=Z8148fba61325d18ed62206940d4cf388\" data-learningcard-id=\"VP0GdT\" data-anker=\"Z8148fba61325d18ed62206940d4cf388\" data-section-id=\"R9clMe0\" data-sememe-id=\"si0tGf\">multinucleated giant cells</a> on <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z590a196481a423510706f3f06332ab86\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z590a196481a423510706f3f06332ab86\" data-section-id=\"ttcX2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"_xa5_5\">Tzanck smear</a> are characteristic of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mL0Vyg&anker=Zc3361a82e3639c04c0b9719824b374bd\" data-learningcard-id=\"mL0Vyg\" data-anker=\"Zc3361a82e3639c04c0b9719824b374bd\" data-sememe-id=\"JBYsb7\">herpes simplex virus infection</a>. While <span data-sememe-id=\"yE1dyi0\">HSV</span> can cause recurrent oral and genital <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulcers</span>, it does not explain the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=JO0stT&anker=Zd5d2643ba7468816c97698c34922eabe\" data-learningcard-id=\"JO0stT\" data-anker=\"Zd5d2643ba7468816c97698c34922eabe\" data-section-id=\"ywXdlZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"azaQrM\">uveitis</a> and the clinical pattern described in this patient.</div>",
